If you know of a better or easier way, please let us know.
This has been a relatively easy approach.

--------------
Installation
--------------

git clone git://github.com/mmullis/coverize.git coverize
cd coverize
make

# Add coverize to your Erlang libraries by either symlinking
# or adding it to the ERL_LIBS environment var
# For example:
export ERL_LIBS=<path to coverize home>:$ERL_LIBS


--------------
Updating
--------------
cd <YOUR ERLANG INSTALLATION LIB DIRECTORY>/coverize
git pull origin master
make clean
make

